         <abstract>
            <p>A wind powered space heating system was installed in a low-energy house on North Ronaldsay, Orkney, using electrical heating of a hot water store. This installation was assisted by occasional passive solar heating. Tests were carried out from March to October 1988, yielding an overall system efficiency of 64%, and readings were taken to investigate the correlation of windspeed data with those obtained at Kirkwall Airport.</p>
         </abstract>
